column5: This article appeared in today's Yellowknife paper. Pretty good sized poike!!!
Is Mike on this forum, know him from roughfish , awesome guy & fantastic for him!
Thats a mighty gator for sure!!!
I've seen smaller Gators in the Everglades. She is one hefty beasty. How old would a fish like that be to get that large way up in God's country?
Hard to say how old it is. It really depends on the lake. We have a lake in town that grows fish quickly because it's warm compared to the larger lakes around.
That is a massive fish! i live in the wrong province lol.
a fish that size on great slave has got to be at least 30 years old.  Incredible. That thing makes the  trophy musky i see guys catch look like dinks.
This one was caught in a tiny little lake here in town. Pretty hard to see exactly how big it is but look @ the head on this beast. It could swallow that kid whole!!!!
